        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3789849304" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4974442087365129336">I feel like I&apos;m getting close to finishing the Miss Marple series but I honestly don&apos;t know. There&apos;s just something about Marple that makes these book so freaking easy to devour. These books are just that dangerous but I am enjoying them from time to time. <br/><br/>The thing with <i>The Mirror Crack&apos;d from Side to Side</i> was that I had way too many suspects and not enough time to be patient enough to figure out who actually did it. So, I kind of just went with the flow of things and waited for the big surpris</span>
  <span id="freeText4974442087365129336" style="display:none">I feel like I'm getting close to finishing the Miss Marple series but I honestly don't know. There's just something about Marple that makes these book so freaking easy to devour. These books are just that dangerous but I am enjoying them from time to time. <br /><br />The thing with <i>The Mirror Crack'd from Side to Side</i> was that I had way too many suspects and not enough time to be patient enough to figure out who actually did it. So, I kind of just went with the flow of things and waited for the big surprise at the end. What I didn't expect was the actual ending of this one. It was just so sad and I felt bad for Marina.<br /><br />I won't go into such great detail about why just know that I was and still am sad for her. What she went through and the reason as to why was just a shock to me as it was to her. In the end, this mystery book was very easy to devour and I look forward to the next one.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4974442087365129336" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
