    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2420320800" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2420320800" />
    <a title="Kavita" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5858699-kavita"><img alt="Kavita" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1315387023p2/5858699.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2420320800?book_show_action=true">Jul 28, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kavita" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kavita" href="/user/show/5858699-kavita">Kavita</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audiobook 9780007115266" href="/book/show/1121698.The_Mirror_Crack_d_From_Side_To_Side">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5858699-kavita?shelf=mystery">mystery</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5858699-kavita?shelf=uk">uk</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2420320800" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16096705679150828986">Another quintessential Marple mystery! A well-meaning but interfering and self-centred woman from the development near St Mary&apos;s Mead falls dead at a party given by Marina Gregg. The American actress has taken the old Bantry house on rent and is trying to make a go of it in English village life with the party.<br/><br/>Thus Mrs. Bantry is invited to the party and sees Heather Badcock dying. The question soon arises whether she was the intended victim? Mrs. Bantry wonders if Jane Marple needs to be consult</span>
  <span id="freeText16096705679150828986" style="display:none">Another quintessential Marple mystery! A well-meaning but interfering and self-centred woman from the development near St Mary's Mead falls dead at a party given by Marina Gregg. The American actress has taken the old Bantry house on rent and is trying to make a go of it in English village life with the party.<br /><br />Thus Mrs. Bantry is invited to the party and sees Heather Badcock dying. The question soon arises whether she was the intended victim? Mrs. Bantry wonders if Jane Marple needs to be consulted and circumstances soon lead her to a positive conclusion. Marple get involved and is able to solve the mystery merely by reading the film magazines. Okay, that was an exaggeration, but barely so! <br /><br />The village has changed beyond recognition in the post-war years and it is one of Miss Marple's challenges to overcome these changes and understand the human nature behind them. It is also a different kind of people she has to deal with - rich Americans. It takes Miss Marple a while to get behind the cultural facade to the inner core of human beings, which are the same everywhere. <br /><br /><i>The Mirror Cracked From Side To Side</i> cheats a little as it is basically impossible to guess the murderer and the motive. But it is a really good book of the armchair detective genre, with Marple hardly moving out of her home much. The daily quibbles of village life, which make these Marples so intriguing are there in full flow in this book too. <br /><br />Another one of my favourites, especially since there are so few set in the village itself.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16096705679150828986" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

